_header: Where is this Prince that conquered his right
Subjects: Edward IV, death of; historical poems
_description: On the Death of Edward IV (1483) — ten stanzas rhyme royal

RylandsEng113.First Lines:
Whar is this Prynce that conquered his rightWithin Ingland master
                    of all his ffoonAnd after ffraunce be very force & myghtWithout
                    stroke and afterward com hoom…
RylandsEng113.Last Lines:
…This knowe ye well he was here yestirdayAll men of Englond ar
                    bounde for hym to pray
